@wordwrap
@tab 8
   
@node sect0 "Name"
listbasic - Extract the BASIC from a ZX Spectrum file    
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
 @{b}listbasic@{ub} @{i}file@{ui}     


@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
listbasic extracts the BASIC listing from a ZX Spectrum snapshot or tape file and prints it to standard output.    
@endnode

@node sect3 "Options"


· @{i}-b@{ui} @{lindent 3}
specifies that the program to list is a Beta BASIC program. @{lindent 0}

· @{i}file@{ui} @{lindent 3}
specifies a snapshot or tape image from which to extract the BASIC, which must be in a format supported by @{i}libspectrum@{ui}(3).    @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect4 "Bugs"
None known.    
@endnode

@node sect5 "See Also"
@{i}fuse@{ui}(1), @{i}fuse-utils@{ui}(1), @{i}libspectrum@{ui}(3) The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{i}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{ui}.    


@endnode

@node sect6 "Author"
Philip Kendall (philip-fuse@shadowmagic.org.uk). Chris Cowley wrote  @{i}SnapList@{ui}, (@{i}http://freestuff.grok.co.uk/snaplist/index.html@{ui}), @{i}@{ui} on which listbasic is very heavily based. 


@endnode
